## Third-party content attribution

This repository's `security-review` skill is informed by patterns documented in
the Arcanum-Sec/sec-context taxonomy:
https://github.com/Arcanum-Sec/sec-context

That work is licensed CC BY 4.0 and is the work of Jason Haddix and Arcanum
Information Security. Pattern selection and ranking informed by that taxonomy
is attributed in the skill's source files.

This repository's commit-time hardening pattern (PostToolUse SAST feedback loop)
adapts the methodology described in:

  Liu, H., Einstein, L., Yang, J., et al. (2026). SecureForge: Finding and
  Preventing Vulnerabilities in LLM-Generated Code via Prompt Optimization.
  arXiv:2605.08382. https://github.com/sisl/SecureForge

SecureForge is MIT-licensed. The implementation in this repo is independent
and does not include SecureForge source code directly.
